Class KnapsackModule

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Module

    @Citation(authors="Eckart Zitzler and Lothar Thiele",
          title="Multiobjective evolutionary algorithms: A comparative case study and the strength Pareto approach",
          journal="IEEE Transactions on Evolutionary Computation",
          volume=3,
          number=4,
          pageFirst=257,
          pageLast=271,
          month=NOVEMBER,
          year=1999)
public class KnapsackModule
extends ProblemModule
    The multiobjective 0/1 ILP knapsack problem as proposed in Zitzler and Thiele 1999. Either one of the nine benchmark problems from Zitzler and Thiele 1999 can be selected or the number of knapsacks and items can be set manually.
    See Also:
    http://www.tik.ee.ethz.ch/sop/download/supplementary/testProblemSuite/
